\end{equation}
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta k = 2\pi/L$
\end_inset

 is the difference between successive values of 
\begin_inset Formula $k_n$
\end_inset

. We now define a function 
\begin_inset Formula $F(k)$
\end_inset

 as
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
	F(k) \equiv \Lim{L \rightarrow \infty} L c_n = \Lim{L \rightarrow \infty} L c_{kL/2 \pi}
	\label{eq:DefFourierTransform}
\end{equation}
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Combining this definition with Eq. 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
